This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with stereo matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. The use of mean field approximations also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to energy minimization, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of MRF models could also suggest a graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and optimization, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
